# Renderer ŌĆö Vector Rendering Layer

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `renderer.py` | `CrossSectionRenderer` facade; dispatches to layout mixins |
| `renderer_common.py` | `RendererGeometryMixin` ŌĆö wells, profile lookup, style resolution |
| `renderer_section_sheet.py` | `SectionSheetLayoutMixin` ŌĆö Strater-like section sheet |
| `renderer_chart.py` | `ChartLayoutMixin` ŌĆö legacy debug chart |
| `renderer_consulting.py` | `ConsultingLayoutMixin` ŌĆö report sheet, title block, screens/gradients |

Input: `GeologicalPolygon` list, projected DataFrame, optional `WaterLevel` / screens / gradients.
Output: Matplotlib figure or SVG/PNG/PDF bytes.

**No projection or pinch-out logic** ŌĆö consume pre-built polygons and projected intervals only.
Lithology fills use the **BH Log** legend (Excel ŌåÆ `constants.get_lithology_style()`; namespaced as `USGS_LITHOLOGY_*`).

## Render Profiles (`render_profiles.py`)

`CrossSectionRenderProfile` controls layout without a second renderer:

| Field | Section sheet (default) | Consulting section | Chart (legacy) |
|-------|-------------------------|-------------------|----------------|
| `layout` | `section_sheet` | `consulting_section` | `chart` |
| `track_width_m` | 3.0 | 1.2 (white columns) | 1.6 |
| `show_track_lithology` | true | false | true |
| `show_grid` / `show_report_grid` | false | report grid (1 m / 10 m) | true |
| `show_ground_surface` / `show_sky_fill` | true / true | true / false | false |
| `show_contact_ticks` / `show_eol_bar` / `show_track_border` | true | false | false |
| `show_column_headers` | true | false (IDs above plot) | false |
| `show_dual_y_axes` | false | true | false |
| `legend_in_title_block` | false | true | false |
| `y_axis_mode` | `elevation_rl` or `depth_below_collar` | `elevation_rl` | `elevation_rl` |
| `water_symbol` | triangle | triangle (labeled RL) | circle |
| `title_block` / `show_ve_annotation` | footer metadata / in-plot | subtitle band + footer legend | false |

Wire profile via `pipeline.build_cross_section(render_layout=..., elevation_mode=...)` or `CrossSectionRenderer(render_profile=...)`.
Theme colors live in `render_theme.py`.

## Interpretation Modes

| Mode | Polygons | Inter-hole fill | Disclaimer |
|------|----------|-----------------|------------|
| `interpolated` | Yes | Filled fence diagram | "Interpreted fence diagram ŌĆö contacts are linearŌĆ”" |
