Set via `CrossSectionRenderer(interpretation_mode=...)` or `pipeline.build_cross_section(interpretation_mode=...)`.

## Section-Sheet Layers (z-order, Strater-like)

1. **Sky fill** ŌĆö light fill above interpolated ground surface (`show_sky_fill`)
2. **Fence polygons** ŌĆö BH Log colors/hatches; lower alpha (`fence_alpha` ~0.58) so tracks read in front
3. **Uncertainty zones** ŌĆö amber shading when spacing/offset thresholds exceeded
4. **Track lithology** ŌĆö wide bordered rectangles per interval inside each borehole track
5. **Track borders** ŌĆö white column outline from collar to TD
6. **Contact ticks** ŌĆö horizontal lines at interval tops/bottoms across track width
7. **Deviated centerlines** ŌĆö dotted polyline through interval midpoints when deviation survey present
8. **Raster log strips** ŌĆö optional placeholder/image column (`RasterLogStrip` model)
9. **Ground surface** ŌĆö thick green/brown polyline
10. **Water table** ŌĆö symbol per hole (circle/triangle/diamond) + optional dashed interpolation
11. **EOL bars** ŌĆö horizontal end-of-log marker at TD
12. **Column headers** ŌĆö hole ID, RL or depth label, TD above each track
13. **Faults / unconformities / environmental markers**
14. **Overlap markers** ŌĆö when `overlap_pairs` provided
15. **Scale bar** + **VE annotation** (`V.E. N├Ś`)
16. **Legend** ŌĆö lithology codes (when `show_legend=True`)
17. **Title block footer** ŌĆö disclaimer + `SectionFigureMetadata` (CRS, datum, azimuth, VE, hole count)

## Chart Layout (legacy debug)

Thin center sticks, optional dashed grid, floating bbox labels, no sky/EOL/contact ticks. Use `CHART_PROFILE` or `render_layout="chart"`.

## Consulting Section Layout (EcoVenture-style report sheet)

Fence-first layout matching consulting cross-section figures (`render_layout="consulting_section"`). Uses `GridSpec`: plot (~62%), subtitle band (~8%), simplified title block (~22%).

**Plot layers (z-order):**

1. **Report grid** ŌĆö 1 m elevation / 10 m distance majors; dual **ELEVATION (m)** axes
2. **Fence polygons** ŌĆö opaque fills (`fence_alpha=1.0`); no wide track lithology
3. **Ground surface** ŌĆö interpolated collar polyline (no sky fill)
4. **Thin well sticks** ŌĆö vertical lines collar to TD (white column fill `TRACK_FILL_COLOR`)
5. **Screen intervals** ŌĆö opaque `TRACK_FILL_COLOR` + `hatch="///"` (Matplotlib needs a non-transparent face for hatch); legend swatch matches
6. **Gradients** ŌĆö vertical arrows when provided
7. **Hole ID labels** ŌĆö above each stick
8. **Transect end labels** ŌĆö optional via `ConsultingTitleBlock`
9. **Water table** ŌĆö labeled RL at each Ō¢╝; dashed interpolation when Ōēź2 points
10. **Faults / unconformities / environmental markers**

**Subtitle band:** section label, `SCALE {map_scale}`, `{VE}├Ś VERTICAL EXAGGERATION`, graphic scale bar.

**Title block:** lithology swatches + GW symbol key + project metadata (`ConsultingTitleBlock` via `SectionBuildRequest.consulting_title_block`).

Wire via `pipeline.build_cross_section(render_layout="consulting_section", consulting_title_block=...)`.
Streamlit: layout radio **Consulting section** + **Report sheet (consulting)** expander.

## Visual Requirements

- Fill polygons via `matplotlib.patches.Polygon` using `constants.get_lithology_style()` (BH Log palette)
- User overrides via `paths.lithology_styles_path()` (user data dir, not repo `data/`)
- Expose **`vertical_exaggeration`** (Y-axis multiplier) and **`scale_bar_length_m`**
- Hatch patterns toggled via `show_hatches`

## Y-Axis Modes

- `elevation_rl` ŌĆö absolute reduced level (default)
- `depth_below_collar` ŌĆö inverted depth axis; wired from UI `elevation_mode=relative`

## Export

- `to_svg_bytes()` / `to_png_bytes(dpi=300)` on rendered figure
- `export_figure_bytes(figure, export_formats, ...)` ŌĆö single figure, selective encoding via `export_formats`
- `pipeline.build_cross_section(export_formats=...)` returns SVG/PNG/PDF bytes per format set (default `{"svg"}` for tests)
- Streamlit Generate: `cached_build_section()` is **SVG-only**; PNG/PDF via `cached_build_section_exports()` after **Prepare**
- `report_export.export_section_pdf()` ŌĆö page 1 section, page 2 legend/metadata/QA summary; reuses `section_figure` when provided
- Allowed: import stratigraphy **types** (`GeologicalPolygon`, `PolygonOverlap`) ŌĆö not correlation/pinch-out logic
